Burlington Industries Inc is raising 75mln dlrs through an offering of convertible subordinateddebentures due 2012 with a 6-1/4 pct coupon and par pricing,said lead manager Kidder, Peabody and Co Inc.    The debentures are convertible into the company's commonstock at 63.50 dlrs per share, representing a premium of 18.1pct over the stock price when terms on the debt were set.    Non-callable for three years, the issue is rated Ba-2 byMoody's Investors Service Inc and BBB by Standard and Poor'sCorp. Merrill Lynch Capital Markets and Salomon Brothers Incco-managed the deal. Reuter&#3;